{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r747618087", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Fabulous ambience and delightful service from Roxanne!", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "25 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Hopesprings1", "reviewer_origin": ["Sunningdale, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r747618087-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Fabulous food, service and old school live Jazz band serenade over dinner - even on a Tuesday night!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r744514687", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Upscale McDonalds ", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "12 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "futtock21", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2802"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1252"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r744514687-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Boisdale Canary Wharf is part of a coterie of British restaurants in London, the others in Belgravia, Bishopsgate and Mayfair. It is a large old-fashioned clubby sort of place spread over a corner of the first and second floors within the Canada Place skyscraper. There is a space for live music at the darkened end of the upper floor restaurant with views over Canada Square. The walls are covered with prints and pictures including some striking female nudes. As this is a Scottish restaurant the waitress wears a short kilt, fishnet tights and a sporran. It also comes with a lifestyle magazine for sales of gin and whiskey edited by Boisdale\u2019s founder Ranald (sic) McDonald. That Scottish delicacy of hamburgers features heavily on a menu that probably hasn\u2019t changed much from the 1980s when Boisdale first opened. Without a 50% discount on food it\u2019s all quite expensive, solid rather than inspiring British cuisine whilst being far from a fine-dining experience. Think sausages and mash, steak and chips, bubble and squeak. I started with a suitably retro cocktail with saucy shrimps as well as larger prawns with added shards of lobster on a bed of creamy lettuce and slaw. Probably slightly inferior to an equivalent I recently enjoyed in a fish restaurant in Hull. I followed this with the dish du jour calves\u2019 liver and bacon on a bed of creamy mash. The liver was very slightly more cooked than the medium rare I had ordered; clusters of bacon much more so. Best of all was an iced nougat dessert with blobs of apple pur\u00e9e. There are some beers on draught as well as in bottles but not on an extensive wine list with at least one bottle over the \u00a32000 mark suggesting pretensions that the food simply doesn\u2019t match."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r743436725", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Good night out!", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "6 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Jan S", "reviewer_origin": ["Hornchurch, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "94"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "54"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r743436725-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["My first visit to Boisdale. I visited on a Friday night - Soul Night! The bar was busy, but not crowded, with inside and outside space.", "The music was great and the place had a good atmosphere. As you'd probably expect, drinks here aren't cheap - cocktails from \u00a312.50, with a spirit and mixer roughly the same (although available from \u00a310 upwards).", "The bar staff were professional and all in all a brilliant night out."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r743081178", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Very good, will return", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "4 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "tripbiscuit", "reviewer_origin": ["London, UK"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "113"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "83"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r743081178-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I took advantage of a groupon offer as I was meeting a friend who lives nearby and we wanted to see what the place was like. We've both passed it many times on the way to somewhere else, but because it's above street level it's hard to know what's up there. ", "Anyway, it's a very nice space, upmarket brasserie-style, with some tables overlooking Cabot Square. It looks as if they can cater for private parties and larger groups. ", "Service was charming and attentive, the wine list goes from low in price (for London), with some interesting bin ends, to pretty high - so something for everyone. Cocktails, aperitifs, dessert wines, whiskies etc etc all look interesting. ", "We asked for our chateaubriand to be served rare and it was beautifully cooked, with large portions. We didn't need to ask for the bottomless chips as our initial serving was generous, and there was good quality bread and butter on the table. Our side of garlic & chili mushrooms was also well above normal quality. ", "The dining room wasn't too full but it had a buzzy atmosphere and I imagine it would be a good place to see live music. It was unfortunate that we didn't have much time to spare otherwise I'd have liked to have stayed to see the blues band that was warming up on stage. The tables that don't have a good view of the stage have screens, so everyone can see. Also, the dining room is so large that the music probably won't be overwhelming if you're not there for that.", "The groupon deal is amazing value; it's a great way to discover a place you've never been before. I arrived early so had time to look at the a la carte menu posted outside which offers a good choice, and the cheese trolley looked varied and interesting. I will definitely be back when I have more time, to try some different things and to see some music."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r744537071", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Boisdale", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "12 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "grahamm586", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r744537071-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Not very busy when we visited. Service pretty slow and the waiter was over familiar and used language not acceptable to the type of restaurant it is. Food ok but not outstanding for the price."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r745107052", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "A pleasant surprise", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "14 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "vickilovesluxury", "reviewer_origin": ["essex"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "201"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "103"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r745107052-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I booked this Friday soul night for me and partner for valentines, I had never been before , we parked in Cabot square and it was very near we didn\u2019t know what to expect but it was a pleasant surprise, it was rocking great music we had a 3 course Meal a few cocktails could have gone to the bar and had a boogie if we had the energy , great service can\u2019t fault it , well if I\u2019m being picky the sirloin steak was a bit tough but all in all a really great place to go"]}
