{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r746994930", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Me and my family came here", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "23 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "113florencel", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r746994930-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Me and my family came here for Sunday brunch today to celebrate my Dad\u2019s birthday with some live music. The music was good but everything else was very disappointing. The waiter struggled to understand what we were saying and really struggled to take our order. They were slow to bring wine / serve us drinks. Our starters were then slow in coming too, luke warm at best and on not the cleanest plates. Having arrived at 1:15pm we were served our mains at 3:30pm! My main was the cod which was rubbery and dry and and missing a key ingredient - chorizo. My dad has the pasta which was tasteless and everyone else had a roast which was okay. They then didn\u2019t have the dessert I ordered which was the chocolate brownie so i ordered ice cream and was served sorbet. All in all a disaster and I can\u2019t believe this place is still going and was as busy as it was, do not waste your money coming here! "]}
