{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r728858552", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "10/10 Excellent", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "25 November 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "swcfc0301", "reviewer_origin": ["Braintree, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "5"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "8"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r728858552-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Excellent food and service with a great musical performance by Alexander O\u2019Neill. Our waiter was very attentive making sure our glasses were kept topped up and we never had to wait to ask for a drink. The food was excellent and once again the waiter excelled himself with his recommendations. Strongly recommend the Barbary duck if you are visiting on Friday. The entertainment was spot on and was a trip down memory lane listening to Alexander O\u2019Neal belt out all of his hits. A top class venue and thoroughly recommended. I feel I have to mention the complete idiot (the man with the grey hair) who sat a couple of tables away with his friend and their two partners. The way in which he spoke to the waitress was just down right ignorant ... apparently he had to wait 32 minutes for his food. BIG DEAL - doesn\u2019t give him an excuse to belittle a young lady and young man who were trying to appease him. Then the way he treated the manager was just rude - if it was me I\u2019d have told him where to go but Wael the Restaurant Manager went above and beyond to try an resolve the problem. Then to top it all Mr Big and his entourage stood in the aisle dancing and obscured the view. Fortunately the sideshow did not spoil a great evening and they thankfully departed when the 80s music came on afterwards and we continued to have a great night. Thank you Wael for the complimentary drinks - we will definitely be coming back."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r734595817", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Dreadful Suday Lunch", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "25 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "gg-ioan", "reviewer_origin": ["Chiswick, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r734595817-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We booked this restaurant few weeks in advance intended for a birthday with our family, the music and food was very good, service wise I can tell was disappointing, as soon we finished our main courses, we was waiting for the celebration cake that we booked in advance for 4 weeks and our server that I belive was even a manager Alberto he delivered to the table near as. I cannot express our dissatisfaction for the whole experience when I saw this. I wish we could have booked somewhere else..."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r730028545", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Re-vamp Artistes!", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "1 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "lyd678", "reviewer_origin": ["Greater London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "53"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "20"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r730028545-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Boisdale, Canary Wharf has been one of my favourite Venues in London since opening. The Food is good, the staff very friendly & efficient, the artistes are very good as is the sound system. Unfortunately after having booked a premium table on the night Alexander O' Neal was appearing left me rather sad. It was the worse artiste I have ever seen appear at Boisdale, he performed one of the shortest sets, sounded awful, then disappeared off the stage for 10 minutes while the band \"played on\" ..Really? ...then to see he is also booked for another two gigs? Come on, Boisdale, you can put on better than that.."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r728430538", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Groupon voucher", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "23 November 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "JamesPLee", "reviewer_origin": ["Sleaford, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "45"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "14"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r728430538-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["So I bought the steak deal for \u00a348 as we were staying in Poplar nearby and shopping in Canary wharf. The food was delicious, we opted out the music and bought a bottle of white wine to go with it. The final bill Inc the money already paid came to \u00a392, the bottle of water was \u00a34.50, wine (cheapest) was \u00a329.50 and service charge \u00a310.25. I like to decide my tip but being English didn't complain.b"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r729619507", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Lovely lunch, great service", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "29 November 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Sue M", "reviewer_origin": ["Croydon, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "716"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "338"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r729619507-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["This was in the grill/bar area, on the first floor. We have been to the Sunday jazz lunch before, which was fabulous, but this was different - low key, but first class. Very similar menu (if not the same) - excellent haggis starter and, although we were on a voucher deal, we paid \u00a310 each extra for the fillet, for main course, and it was well worth it - absolutely delicious! The Irish, Bulgarian and Moldovan staff, who looked after us, were delightful and charming. We couldn't have asked for a better lunch experience in Canary Wharf. Definitely will go again."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r731364155", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "I booked this restaurant intended", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "8 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "VirtuousWoman777", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r731364155-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I booked this restaurant intended for a nice evening with my boyfriend for his birthday. Previously I have been to Boisdale but didn\u2019t realise that their were multiple levels for dinner and music. On this occasion it was the first floor. It wasn\u2019t as I expected. We accepted that the table location wouldn\u2019t be the intimate setting we hoped for. Starters, good. Waiters checked on us thus far, service was flowing nicely again thus far, good. Heard some RnB playing in the background but thought it was a prelude and the artist of the night would be on shortly as my purchase promised. ", "Mains arrived and it was burnt. We ordered the burger as it was safe. No check backs by waiters kinda told me that, not only they were aware but avoiding what had happened. I didn\u2019t eat it and later told the waiter that finally checked on us later that night. Nothing was done. We advised him to skip desert as it was already going sour in my view. He encouraged us to hang on as we mind change our minds. We didn\u2019t change our minds as the music I hoped for us to enjoy with dinner NEVER came on. ", "Later I approached the till to ask whether I could at least have my desert money back after explaining the situation and was given an outright NO. The guy became so defensive. I even explained that I understood that I should not have waited so long into my meal NOT HAD to mention me being displeased and he shut me down. It was such an unpleasant, UNWELCOMING feeling. So starter good, burnt mains, no dessert, no compensation and a good bye. My service was no longer needed. Oh, and no promised reggae music DJ person which was included in my \u00a329.99. Apparently they were on from after 10pm and not from 0715pm as stated with my purchase. ", "I would never hesitate to mention that after I was treated the way I was, I was offered a card for my next visit to Boisdale for some future compensation, shocking!!!! I asked the gentleman to put himself in my shoes, if you had a dining experience with such poor treatment, will you return? Thanks to him for putting the cider and glass of milk with mint leaf (aka pina colada) on the house but I think if customers views, feedbacks and right to get issues rectified aren\u2019t welcome, then please DO NOT TAKE our monies, and especially if you cannot deliver. ", "Buyers, Boisdale is a beautiful venue for fine dining and fun, lovely music, beautiful ambiance depending on the floor level you select i suppose. I have experienced it previously, 2nd FLOOR ONLY. But unfortunately, this reggae DJ night (which was no where in sight) and Jamaican food situation going on the first floor was delivered poorly. Maybe it was just on our night but the end treatment we were given made us feel so unwelcomed and so \u2018whether or not you return, bothers us not\u2019. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r733223522", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Nowadays, a sad old clip joint", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "17 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "marklE2664GC", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "21"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "19"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "40", "10"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r733223522-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["This place has gone to pot. It has come to resemble the worst kind of Soho clip joint", "from the bad old days.", "The food came more than an hour late and was of poor quality. The drinks were sharply marked up. The place was mostly empty. no more needs to be said"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r733228124", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "David 82rd Birthday ", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "17 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "447marcioteixe", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r733228124-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I love boisdale dearly i really have a softspot for this place. Boisdale is a place very vers\u00e1til on way of have a Romantic Between 2 or a lovely gadering time with family and friends. We had amazing 3 courses meal . I definetely enjoyed my stake and sl everyone . The staff are well friendly and very attentive . The singer was superb. What a talent . Thank to the menage Weal that he personaly was making sure our experience should be up to our standart. Once again thank you to everyone who contribute to our best Boisdale Experience. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r722197593", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Nice relaxing venue", "diner_date": " October 2019", "rating_date": "29 October 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Downba", "reviewer_origin": ["Thurrock, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "184"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "62"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r722197593-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Loved it here, a little hard to find but we were all wowed once we got inside. Lovely decor and atmosphere with a Jazz band playing In the background. Huge whiskey menu plus a Huge wall full of drinks. Lovely views if you are lucky to get a window seat. Sunday menu not huge but enough to choose from. Squid was very tasty., Beef was very good maybe a little fatty but that didn\u2019t stop it being very tasty. Huge portions with plenty of veg. You had to pay extra for the cheese which I thought was a little unfair as the food isn\u2019t cheap. All in all a great place which is excellent for a special occasion and I will definitely return at some point"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r728141861", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Fab atmosphere at Alexander", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "22 November 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "TerriH912", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "21"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "10"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r728141861-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Fab atmosphere at Alexander O\u2019Neal evening! Plenty of god music, excellent view of the stage and plenty of dancing!", "Food was fabulous, up there with the best I\u2019ve tasted and oysters were the best I\u2019ve had!", "Wines a bit pricey but the norm for a restaurant ", "Will defo be returning "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r721457040", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "wonderful ambience", "diner_date": " October 2019", "rating_date": "26 October 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Dawn P", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "164"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "50"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r721457040-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Open table had 50% off for 7pm slot on a Friday night. Had drink in bar downstairs to restaurant first, it was very busy. Mixed age group.", " Al A Carte Food choice good. Everything ordered was tasty and hot. starters of Chilli squid was yum. Scottish salmon looked lush. Mains one haggis, burger x 2 , cod loin.", "Portion sizes good. Waiter was professional and friendly. 12.5% service charge added. If we had stayed seated after 9/30 we would have been charged \u00a315.00 per person in our food bill but this was explained. We chose not to stay. Definitely return. They have Rat Pack Xmas show with dinner which may be of interest."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r718691518", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Superb food : highly recommended.", "diner_date": " October 2019", "rating_date": "15 October 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "PlanksConstant", "reviewer_origin": ["Bracknell, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "31"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "8"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r718691518-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I had the 2 course set menu, beef steak and it was superb. Thick and succulent all the way through.", "The set menu was very limited in options and I found it difficult to chose between the options. But I think everything we had was very good, and I wondered if their strategy is present a limited menu but do it well.", " I chose not to have the fries with cheese but soon regretted it: the thrice cooked chips are coated in truffle oil and the simple description on the menu tells you absolutely nothing about the taste or quality. Unbelievable flavour. I'm a middle aged guy , been out to many restaurants in my time, but the favour of these fries is unique and superb.", "For desert I opted for the Orange sorbet which was of unbelievable quality.", "Whiskey: the whiskey menu is a book over 30 pages long! Where do you start? ! It was dark and very hard to read, and it just wasn't clear if they were selling it by the glass (single or double measures) or only by the bottle. These are top quality malt whiskeys costing a lot of money. One bottle of whiskey in a display cabinet near the entrance was priced at \u00a3250! In the end I didn't for a drink."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r726422891", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "MI SOUL TUNES WITH BOISDALE DINNER", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "14 November 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "JoycelynPhillips", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "82"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "16"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r726422891-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["heard a lot of good things about The Boisdale & the amazing DJs from Mi Soul. I wasn't disappointed with the music which was made for dancing!!", "The two course dinner was just above average but very affordable. Service was attentive & friendly.", "I would definitely go again for the music but I think the full priced menu will be more appetising!!!"]}
