{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r707860180", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great Sunday lunch", "diner_date": " September 2019", "rating_date": "8 September 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Ivor B", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "5"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r707860180-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Just got home from a Sunday lunch at Boisdale Canary Wharf. What a great way to spend a Sunday afternoon:", "Food -we all had the roast beef as a main course, and for the first time ever, when my wife offered me the beef she couldn't finish, I had to turn her down as I was full. Superb roast.", "Service: Andrea our waitress was terrific - we had our 8 month old grandson with us, and nothing was too much trouble.", "Music - lovely jazz trio playing all the greats, and finished with one of my favourites - C jam blues.", "Atmosphere - just great.", "Cost - not cheap, but worth every penny for such a lovely afternoon.", "Will be back soon", "PS did I mention the cheese?"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r704206425", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "One of my favourite restaurants", "diner_date": " March 2019", "rating_date": "29 August 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "gachilleos", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "16"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "7"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r704206425-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["The Canary Wharf Boisdale has to be one of my favourite restaurants in London. Apart from the great view that you get of the Thames and surrounding area, the food is amazing!", "Boisdale is split into 2 floor; The first floor containing the bar and cigar lounge & balcony and the top floor containing the restaurant. The restaurant serves amazing food whether it's meat or seafood and often have live music which is a bonus. ", "When we've finished our dinner we often go downstairs to the balcony where we have a nice cigar and coffee to wind down our evening."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r709928253", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Husbands 50th birthday", "diner_date": " September 2019", "rating_date": "15 September 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "donnabT8796GB", "reviewer_origin": ["Greater London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "7"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "11"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r709928253-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Visited Boisdale on a Saturday evening. Very odd entrance into the venue And then you have no idea where to head , no signs etc. We were in the bar and a very unwelcoming staff member took my name, said we were upstairs but would we like Drink in the bar. So we had a drink and then went up for the meal. Received our menu which looked good until you see that most things had a supplement. Not impressed, it has cost us \u00a3600 for the 6 of us already. With all the supplements we ended up paying an extra \u00a3100. If you have an inclusive price you should have a menu we can select from with the odd supplement. Food and service was very nice. The Barry white entertainment was good but would have liked to hear all the old faves didn\u2019t know most of the songs. The set was very short and the night was over before we knew it. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r696358667", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Birthday Celebrations", "diner_date": " August 2019", "rating_date": "7 August 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "66vivienneb", "reviewer_origin": ["London"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "4"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r696358667-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Variety of dished on the menu, most of which were tasty, as stated by friends. Unfortunately, salt fish fritters too salty. Apart from that everything else was delicious.", "Great atmosphere and service. The staff were really helpful and polite. Would definitely go again."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r689399144", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Tasty, but over-priced and poor service", "diner_date": " July 2019", "rating_date": "14 July 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Hapless-and-Hungry", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "67"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "31"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "20", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r689399144-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We had lunch here on a Friday and it was fairly quiet so we got a nice table by the window. However, despite it being quiet the service was really poor to start with. It took 15 minutes for our drinks order to be taken and even then they got it wrong and had to start again, and it was 35 minutes until our food order was taken. When the food did arrive it was very good, though it would be hard to describe it as good value. ", "If you are a cigar smoker you'll enjoy the walk-in humidor and option to smoke inside in the sampling lounge or out on the terrace. There is a quite spectacular range of whiskey to choose from too. ", "Overall we enjoyed out lunch, but it's not good value and the service let us down on the day (were it not for the poor service we would give it 4 out of 5, but we can only judge it on the experience we had on the day."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r688874071", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Saxone at Boisdale ", "diner_date": " June 2019", "rating_date": "12 July 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "DanaMarie73", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "64"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "39"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r688874071-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I have always found the staff polite and friendly . ", "However on my most recent visit the Restaurant Manager was extremely rude and abrupt. ", "Saxon at Boisdale Canary Wharf.... is a yearly even that my friends and I have been attending since last year summer, we\u2019ve always had a fabulous time.. from the atmosphere, to the food cocktails, service, and staff, couldn\u2019t fault it.", "I booked two free entry tickets on line.. as I have always done,, once there we would find a unreserved table and ordered drinks and a meal from the Jamaican themed set menu.", "However on my previous visit last week... June 29th...: we were extremely disappointed, the restaurant Manager was extremely rude and abrupt. ", "Service ", "We arrived at 5:30pm to find it closed although it opens at 5:30pm... we waited for 10 minutes before the doors opened... as we walked in we didn\u2019t even receive an apology for the wait.... there was a young lady managing the table bookings. She asked my friend and I if we had a table, we told her we had not however would like to order food... as we have always done without the need to book in advance. She smiled at said it wasn\u2019t a problem... The place was empty..however we could see that the majority of the tables inside the restaurant were reserved.. we headed out into the roof terrace where we could see there were quite a few unreserved tables, we were quickly approached by the restaurant manager, he asked if we had a reservation I replied we haven\u2019t,he told us we could only order drinks, I was shocked by this. We\u2019d been on numerous occasions and it wasn\u2019t a problem, I explained this to him ... he then said we could order food but he would need the table in an hour...... by 6:30pm,which I didn\u2019t understand why because there were other empty tables. ", "At around 9pm we were still sat at the table, we had starter, main and dessert, washed down with two cocktails. We were asked to leave the table by the restaurant manager, while we were drinking our cocktails!. I found him very abrupt and rude!. He didn\u2019t even want us to finish our drinks! He presented us with the bill and stood over us as if to rush us to pay.... our waiter was very pleasant and attentive ... the food was presented to a high standard and tasted superb therefore I would have paid the service charge.... however because of the treatment we received by the new restaurant manager I told him to remove it! ", "Food 2 course Menu \u00a319:95", "Slightly changed menu compared to last year. ", "For starter I had Jerk chicken Caesar salad", "parmesan, anchovies, croutons. Main; ", "Char-grilled 6oz Aberdeenshire rib-steak burger, tarragon mayonnaise, dill pickles, red onion, beef tomatoes, Sides: Thrice cooked hand-cut chips. Dessert; White chocolate & nutella truffle 9.50 milk chocolate & hazelnut ganache,white chocolate mousse, caramelised hazelnuts. ", "It all tasted superb 10 out of 10 ", "My friend said all her courses tasted delicious. ", "Our only criticism was the cocktails of reggae rum punch tasted purely of alcohol which was too over powering.... having Jamaican parents and making my own rum rum punch for large family gatherings I would like to think I know what a good rum punch should taste like. ", "We also had a Vanilla Daiquiri which wasn\u2019t very nice. I noticed all the bar staff were different to when we were last there last September. ", "Location ", "Canary Wharf shopping centre. Roof terrace. ", "Overall the experience with one of the managers was extremely unpleasant and quite off putting, he needs to learn how to greet guests on arrival, and make them feel welcomed instead of coming across very obnoxious! ", "The three stars are for the food only, it would have been 4 if it wasn\u2019t for his rudeness and not very well made cocktails. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r689405205", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "\u2018 Brucie bonus \u2018 !!", "diner_date": " July 2019", "rating_date": "14 July 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "233terencef", "reviewer_origin": ["Chelmsford, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "49"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "10"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r689405205-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Made a last minute decision on a Friday to visit somewhere on Canary Wharf. I had heard of Boisdale as a pseudo music and food venue, so thought would give it a go. How lucky were we ! The Luther Vandross inspired show presented by the excellent Fil Straughan was terrific. To call it a tribute denigrates what it was , top draw musicians crafted a great night of live music. Fil is clearly a well rounded singer , he ended with Prince\u2019s Purple Rain \u2018 but he can sing anything I reckon. To give some context , all of my spare cash is spent on music events 17 so far this year of various perceived quality , Elton, Billy Joel , to Golf club crooners - so I think I know performance and talent - Fil is right up there. The food was more than adequate service excellent and the pre- dinner cocktail on level 1 was served with a smile and the 80\u2019s decks was great for my age group. These unexpected pleasures are always the best and I can see us being regular visitors looking at the programme of future events - and especially if Fil returns - then I am bringing a crowd !!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r692670258", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Relaxing and cozy restaurant with live music", "diner_date": " July 2019", "rating_date": "25 July 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "LokSubba", "reviewer_origin": ["Bergen, Norway"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "102"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "27"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r692670258-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Three old friends were roaming around at Canari Wharf, and we needed a cool place to sit and dine on a very hot day in London. We bumped into this restaurant, by chance. It turned out to be a good choice. Cool atmosphere, with live music, and great food. The service was good, too!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r691135369", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Very disappointing", "diner_date": " July 2019", "rating_date": "20 July 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "markfromWales", "reviewer_origin": ["Nyon, Switzerland"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "14"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "13"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r691135369-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We went for a family meal last night. The service was begrudging and charmless. Our warm starters arrived three minutes after our cocktails. Our mains were poor - glorified fast food - really greasy chunky chips.The bread was perfect, though. The steak was rubbery and cold. The scantily-clad young women on roller-blades give this place a weird and anachronistic feel. To be avoided."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r693480626", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Comedy of errors ", "diner_date": " July 2019", "rating_date": "28 July 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "JennyDavidWanstead", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "34"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "15"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r693480626-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["My Wife and I went with Friends for Sunday Lunch , never again. We ordered pre lunch drinks one of which was a Campari and Soda , attempt number one arrived at the table the Soda was poured and then mysteriously disappeared. Attempt number two arrived with at least 5 yes 5 dead flies in it , attempt number three arrived all looking well until the waiter knocked the Soda water over with water everywhere. ", "Starters passed uneventful, the mains were a different story. Every meal bar one was cold. On complaint every meal was taken away and fresh food was presented but the Yorkshire puddings were still cold so they were returned for a second time , I gave up complaining on the third attempt. After the Main course the waiter cleared the table , he managed to spill the vegetables all over my place and seat luckily I wasn\u2019t in it. ", "Lastly they had sold out of the dessert that we wanted. ", "The Management were very aware of their short falls and took the service and an additional 20% of the bill although a nice gesture they need to up their game and be mindful of what comes out of the kitchen and what\u2019s served in its glasses.", "The Jazz though was very good one favourable thing in a very very disappointing lunch. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r695357299", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Beatles night", "diner_date": " August 2019", "rating_date": "4 August 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "mattb664", "reviewer_origin": ["Newcastle upon Tyne, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "12"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "7"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r695357299-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Family of four, mature! We all had a great time \u201cImagine the Beatles\u201d were great. Danced and sang for two hours. Food and service were great. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r694111787", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Upmarket cigar-friendly venue", "diner_date": " March 2019", "rating_date": "30 July 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "jameslW5979AJ", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "42"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "35"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r694111787-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I've been here many times over the last few years and it has always been fairly lively. The food is good, sometimes excellent, but it can also be a bit pricey. The booze is excellent and there's enough bottles of single Malts to kill a rich man's liver. But what a way to go. The decor is plush very Scottish and the food from Scotland Grace's the menu. Live mini haggis starters, salmon, steak and burgers. There's live jazz most nights (Jool Holland is director of music, or something like that). The cigar lounge is where you can taste fine Havanas for as long as you like but cigarettes are a no-no. ", "The downstairs bar is adjacent to a nice smoking terrace. Ranald McDonald who owns the place has been collecting rare vintage photos of famous people for years and they are up on the walls like a photo gallery. It's not cheap to eat and dine and smoke here but it's usually worth it. If you want to enjoy the live music bedt to check it's on before you arrive. Very good place for business groups and City types. Personally I prefer Boisdale Belgravia which is a lot cosier. Worth a punt if you want a special night out. It all depends on the night for it's sometimes quiet. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r694210084", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "West End Jersey Boyz", "diner_date": " July 2019", "rating_date": "30 July 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "412clivep", "reviewer_origin": ["Cheltenham, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "143"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "47"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r694210084-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Had the set 2course menu with extras. Had the Haggis as a starter and the Squid both very tasty and a good size. Mains were Roast sirloin of Gloucester Old spot pork, braised peas, bacon & lettuce, Black Truffle rib-steak hamburger", "watercress, melted Swiss cheese, roast mushrooms and Char-grilled herb marinated free-range chicken breast", "asparagus, pea & heirloom tomato salad, grain mustard & lemon dressing. Had side of Truffle, rosemary & parmesan chips. All were well presented and tasted great.", "Now we did have the 2 course set but added two deserts... Baked passionfruit cheesecake and the 5 cheese cheese board - Shorrock\u2019s Lancashire Bomb, Stinking Bishop, Wigmore Small, Harbourne Blue Half and Colston Bassett. Wow a fantastic selection of cheeses all strong and full flavoured.. Lush!", "The meal was down with Merlot \u201c120\u201d 2017 very acceptable easy drinker.", "The waiter was first class very friendly and attentive.", "The show was brilliant. We had seen the Jersey Boyz show a while back and this was a good pracey. So all in all a great night out. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r687904142", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Amazing!", "diner_date": " June 2019", "rating_date": "8 July 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "whorunstheworld", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r687904142-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Celebrated my birthday here with family and friends on the 29th We were warmley welcomed and my birthday was celebrated with the best service. Wael was outstanding from start to finish and made me feel very special. I can't thank him enough. Food was delicious and was West Indian dining with Reggae/Soul music playing curtosey of Saxon Sound!", "Cocktails were delicious! Great evening. ", " ", "Thank you all we will definitely be back!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r682780706", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "M\u00e9morable !! ", "diner_date": " June 2019", "rating_date": "19 June 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Positivimage", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "8"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r682780706-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["A really relaxed place. Nice bar area and a restaurant on the top floor.. The staff here are externally professional and friendly.", "Brilliant place for private events. Will come back again.", "Thank you to boisdale team for making it a memorable evening! "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r682200048", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Great venue, dreadful food", "diner_date": " June 2019", "rating_date": "17 June 2019", "answer_text": ["Dear DRT46,", "I\u2019m sorry to hear that although you enjoyed the venue, location, d\u00e9cor and the ambience, you found the quality of the food to be disappointing. The matter since has been brought to the attention of our Head Chef.", "Please do get in contact with me at gm@boisdale-cw.co.uk to discuss it further.", "Kind regards", "Tony H."], "reviewer_pseudo": "DRT46", "reviewer_origin": ["Milton Keynes, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "44"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "16"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r682200048-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We bought VIP show tickets to see a Frank Sinatra tribute. Great venue, great location, good decor and ambience, fabulous wine list (not cheap but a great selection). Reception was warm, friendly and helpful. Table service initially was good too.", "We had a fab table right by the stage. The ticket price included dinner (\u00a3125 pp). It was sold as a specialist seafood restaurant, my favourite. The menu however was very limited. Oysters and Lobster were the only seafood and they were all extra (Lobster was +\u00a315!) All sides are extra too starting at \u00a36. The quality of the food was very disappointing. We had chicken and lobster. Both were over cooked and dry. The lobster was tiny, the chicken was tasteless despite being smothered in herbs. ", "No one asked how our food was or offered us any accompaniments. It was hard to get the attention of anyone. ", "Overall we had a great evening as the act was truly world class (Stephen Trevitt is as close to Old Blue Eyes as you\u2019ll ever get).", "I would return but not for food which was a real let down. If this had simply been a restaurant meal I would have given it a rating of terrible. Extremely poor quality and poor value for money. Watch out for the \u201cdiscretionary\u201d service charge!!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r680998626", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Was impressed on my second visit ", "diner_date": " May 2019", "rating_date": "12 June 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "K4395VBcatherinel", "reviewer_origin": ["Worthing, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "201"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "97"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r680998626-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Having had a not so great time here in January I gave it a second chance & we had a lovely evening at the Fleur East concert. The customer service was great, steaks were good & we were served promptly this time around. Nice that the floor manager remembered us & went out of his way to make us feel welcome. Thank you! "]}
