{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r614700273", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Expensive drinks and slow service ", "diner_date": " July 2018", "rating_date": "7 September 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "SamanthaS2308", "reviewer_origin": ["Kent, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "4"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "7"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r614700273-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I went to the Boisdale to watch a musical act play and had pre-booked to sit in the green seats at the back by the entrance. I think we sat under a air conditioning unit as it was freezing. We ordered 2 drinks from the waiter when we were seated and they seemed to take ages to arrive. When it came time to pay I had to run around the venue to find a waiter who then brought us over two more drinks instead of the bill. A 12 % tip was automatically placed on the bill for 2 drinks which I asked to be removed. The musical act was fantastic but I don\u2019t think I would rush back to the venue. "]}
