{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r583229454", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "VIP Mel C Ticket", "diner_date": " May 2018", "rating_date": "28 May 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "anthony w", "reviewer_origin": ["Broadstairs, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "42"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "17"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r583229454-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We loved the intimate closeness of our front seats, The venue is perfect for a special occasion, however the set menu in my opinion was not up to the usual standards, my chicken pie was way to over seasoned with fennel, not very palatable.", "The win and our service was excellent and the bill was as anticipated for 4 dinners.", "However a 12% service charge \"\u00a3140\" was automatically applied to our total bill which included our show ticket cost, this charge is discretionary and I therefor ask for it to be removed, Which our waiter quite understood, showing his own disapproval, I then tipped in the old conventional way for our meal and wine.", "I consider this bad practice unless Mel C got a 12% cut ?"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r584331551", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Unreliable", "diner_date": " June 2018", "rating_date": "1 June 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Winterfrosts", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "16"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "13"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r584331551-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Made a reservation here for a business lunch and arranged all details with client. Then they cancelled my reservation with short notice because they took a private booking. Not impressed by their way of doing business."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r580426777", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Rita Coolidge and her band are a delight", "diner_date": " May 2018", "rating_date": "15 May 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "ItsJustMyOpinion", "reviewer_origin": ["Huntingdon, Cambs"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "75"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "80"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r580426777-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["A great day to visit is on a Monday. It is a quiet day even with someone as famous as Rita Coolidge. We had an excellent table and view of the stage. The venue exudes quality. Boisdale staff were efficient and pleasant, the food was very good but all was surpassed by the music. The band were accomplished as you would expect and Rita sings as well as ever but the overriding impression is how generous they all were with their time to chat and how genuine they all were. It is a credit to Boisdale they can attract such stars and a credit to Rita Coolidge and her band they are willing to play at Boisdale. A wonderful evening that will be long remembered."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r586563309", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Very Disappointing", "diner_date": " June 2018", "rating_date": "11 June 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "jg34", "reviewer_origin": ["UK"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "57"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "74"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "20", "20"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r586563309-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Have been to Boisdales twice before and each time it was exceptional.", "Booked a Frank Sinatra night on Saturday for 4 of us for my husbands birthday. The service was literally non existent. Our waitress was very slow on bringing the wine menu over and taking food orders. The food too ages to arrive and the steaks were not of the best quality. No one checked on us throughout the meal to see if everything was OK - ended up retrieving our wine from the ice bucket they put it in as no one was topping up the wine glasses. ", "Most disappointing of all was that the music from the Reggae Festival below in the bar was over powering the music upstairs - I did complain to the reception - and they did say they would sort it out - but at that point the night had already been spoiled.", "Very disheartened that they seemed to value \u00a320 a head buffet customers more than those of us who had paid \u00a3200 plus for a table."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r585051792", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Fraudulent misselling of VIP tickets", "diner_date": " May 2018", "rating_date": "4 June 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "exil84", "reviewer_origin": ["Berlin, Germany"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "13"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "10", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r585051792-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I visited Boisdale in May 2018 with some friends to attend the Melanie C residency.", "I booked a table for five people more than two months in advance, buying the most expensive option (the so-called 'VIP ticket', 175 \u00a3), in order to be as close as possible to the stage. The restaurant's website advertises the seats as being - I quote - \"within 5 metres from stage (full closest view)\", and I when I placed my order, the person on the phone kindly confirmed that the table was going to be \"literally in front of the stage\". I insisted on this point during the booking, because I knew I would have guests flying from overseas just to see the gig and I wanted it to be perfect - otherwise I would have opted for non-VIP seats. In order to remind the personnel about this aspect, I even wrote an e-mail the day before the event, to ensure our immediate proximity to the stage. ", "When we arrived, we were seated on a table which was way behind the VIP sector. In fact, we were sitting among other Melanie C fans who had bought cheaper tickets. We immediately reported this to the reception staff and we were told that we could stand up and move close to the stage during the performance. Of course, we were not happy at all with this compromise, because WE WERE NOT GIVEN WHAT WE HAD PAID FOR, but we did not want to let this spoil our mood. ", "When the performance started, we got closer to the stage, as we had been told. This was not the most enjoyable experience, and certainly not what we were promised when we bought our tickets, but we thought that it was better than sitting behind three rows of tables and not having a proper view of the concert. (By the way: other fans sitting behind us did the same, so we thought that we could have spent much less money and still see the concert close to the stage!).", "This is where the most upsetting part of the evening began: we were repeatedly told off in quite a rude way by the restaurant staff because we were standing. This impoliteness was absolutely not acceptable. Not only did it collide with the instructions we had received when we were seated, but it had a negative impact on the rest of the evening. We could not enjoy the concert because of the bitterness this whole situation had caused.", "The cherry on top arrived at the end of the dinner, when a waitress came to our table with the bill of another guest who had left the restaurant without paying. We knew him from previous concerts, but this did not mean we had to pay for him! This was not just embarrassing - it was shameless.", "I have written an e-mail to complain about the service and the organisation of the evening and the restaurant manager refused to offer any sort of compensation or even a refund of the price difference between VIP tickets and the seats we were actually given. I believe that a restaurant which aspire to excellence like Boisdale should look after its customers in a more sensible and professional way and take their complaints more seriously.", "The food was good, but on the whole our experience was VERY frustrating."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r574289774", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Amazing wvening", "diner_date": " April 2018", "rating_date": "19 April 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Ravingeddie", "reviewer_origin": ["United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "355"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "179"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r574289774-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Boisdale never disappoints and I haven\u2019t been for a few years.", "There last night to see some great musicians, food, staff was amazing, Ranald runs a great ship there it has to be said..", "Defo a place not to miss out on, even if just pop into the bar for a drink and not the second floor for the music.."]}
