{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r545402070", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "FOOD AND DRINKS OVER-PRICED...GREAT ENTERTAINMENT.", "diner_date": " December 2017", "rating_date": "6 December 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "dollyrocker17", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "50"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "48"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "40", "20"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r545402070-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["So last night 4 of us came to Boisdales for a Xmas get-together. Our waitress Kate was fantastic...friendly and on the ball. My husband ordered 2 large vodka/sodas for us and i can honestly say all we could taste was water. Same thing on our 2nd order...water. We decided to buy a bottle of vodka for \u00a3108.00 thinking it would be cheaper....it was a 75cl bottle what u can buy in a supermarket for \u00a312.00! Moving on....i ordered advacado as a starter....i found 3 small pieces in total amongst a load of green salad! For my main course i ordered Cod....it turned up raw...really unacceptable considering what we were paying for the meal. My husbands rib eye steak was bland and chewy as well. Our 2 friends meals were nothing special either. On the bright side...the Vegas Night was great...but we wont be rushing back for below average food at above average prices and ridiculously priced drinks."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r542631560", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Birthdays ", "diner_date": " November 2017", "rating_date": "22 November 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "josyr-1234", "reviewer_origin": ["Grays Thurrock, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "31"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "23"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r542631560-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We went to the frank sinatra tribute which was good ", "We all ordered steaks which I may add took ages to arrive ", "When they did they was going to walk away still like jelly in the middle and undercooked and we all asked for medium -rare ", "We all 5 of us couldn\u2019t eat it .. ", "the management was very apologetic and asked if we wanted 5 more ", "We really had enough by then ", "So we got a complimentary bottle of wine ", "Still had a good night and it was very busy .. ", "would I return .. ermmm prob yes but I wish they had they had all them silly things in order for a 10/10 "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r544975227", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Worst experience - will not return", "diner_date": " December 2017", "rating_date": "4 December 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "tgordonx", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "11"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "10", "10"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r544975227-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Dear Sirs,", " ", "We visited your restaurant on Friday 1st December for our family Christmas meal, of which there were 9 of us, some of whom had travelled over from Ireland to see family and enjoy a Christmas meal altogether.", " ", "We were booked in for 8:15 and were showed to our tables and left with the menus, after around 20 minutes we were still waiting for a waiter to come and ask if we would like any drinks or wine, so we took it upon ourselves to ask for the wine list, which was duly bought over.", " ", "We then waited another 20 minutes for someone to come and take our drinks order, which included 5 cocktails and 2 bottles of wine. Only the 2 bottles of wine and 2 of the cocktails were brought over. We then waited until 9:15pm and we had to go and speak to the manager to complain that our order had not been taken and that we were still waiting for the other 3 cocktails.", " ", "At around 9:30 our food order was taken, a full hour and 15 minutes after we had sat down.", " ", "When the starters arrived 2 of our table had ordered the rocket watercress and parmesan salad, but instead were given beetroot and goats cheese, something that was not on the menu, and two of our table ordered the avocado salad which had about 2 pieces of avocado in it, but after having to wait for so long we did not want to complain and wait even longer to start eating.", " ", "Once finished we waited a while for the table to be cleared and we did complain to the manager about the starters being incorrect and he did mention he would bring out the correct starters but we said no could we just have our mains. The mains arrived, 3 of us ordered the rib eye steak, from having a rib eye before I would expect to see a bit of fat around the edge to enhance the flavour, but the steaks we were given were half meat and half fat, I will attach a picture to show what we left as it was just fat and gristle. The problem was the steak was tasty just a shame we couldn\u2019t have enjoyed it more.", " ", "We then waited again until about half 11 for our plates to be cleared a full 3 hours and 15 minutes after we had sat down, we were then given the main dessert menu rather then the set menu which we had paid for.", " ", "When the waitress came to take our order I asked for the cheese plate and she said which one so I said there is only one on the set menu and you have given us the incorrect menus which she apologised for and bought over the correct menus for the rest of the table.", " ", "We were finally served our desserts at 5 past Midnight, at which point we had had enough of waiting and didn\u2019t really enjoy them, because it felt like we were eating them for the sake of it as we had already pre-paid for them.", " ", "This is the first time I have been to dinner and had my main one day and my dessert on another day.", " ", "I had been looking forward to visiting your restaurant because I enjoy my whiskey and cigars, so I wanted to try some whiskeys, a couple of weeks ago I tried a Cherry Bourbon and had read on your website you had a vast choice of whiskeys, I asked the ma\u00eetre de if you had a cherry bourbon and he said he was not sure but he would find out, he never came back and told me which I thought was extremely poor form.", " ", "After we had ordered our desserts which was about 11:45pm, myself and another member of our party headed down to the cigar room, which we would have done a lot earlier if we hadn\u2019t of waited nearly 3 hours to finish our mains, when we got to the cigar room they said they were no longer serving, and we could not buy one, so again one of the things I had been looking forward to, I could not enjoy because of the terribly poor service.", " ", "To add to the overall bad service, we had two tables next to us, who appeared to think they were at a football match rather then a good restaurant and it took us to complain 3 or 4 times before anything was actually done with them, even though we were told by one of your waitresses you were trying to get rid of them, but 5 minutes later more drinks and shots were being bought to them. Our table was abused with disgusting language from the table next to us - which I wont repeat on here. After numerous complaints nothing was done till the end of the night when the police removed these people.", " ", "When it came to paying the bill, we had a long conversation with the manager and expressed all of our disappointments throughout the evening and she was kind enough to take off some of the bottles of wine we had ordered and we eventually paid approx. \u00a3187 for our drinks.", " ", "We had previously paid \u00a360 each for the set menu, which for that I would expect good food and good service, I could have had better food and service going to my local Wimpy.", " ", "If you are going to portray yourselves as a high end restaurant at least have the staff and produce to back this up.", " ", "Due to the long delays we had encountered we did not leave the restaurant until 12:30am by which point we had missed our last train home, so we had to order Uber\u2019s to take us home, one of which was \u00a345 and the other was about \u00a330 so this was an extra \u00a375 we had to pay out as a group due to your poor service.", " ", "We really expected more from this night, and if we had not already pre-paid for the meal we would have walked out before ordering our starters because of the length of time it took to order, I appreciate if it was a busy night, but you do these music evenings fairly often so you should be used to dealing with a full cover of tables.", " ", "Also, we could not enjoy the music on offer, as were having to eat our starters and mains as the entertainment reached its pinnacle due to the long delays we encountered throughout the evening", " ", "Both myself and my partner would not visit your restaurant again and I think I speak for the remainder of the party as well.", " ", "I also work in the City and am quite near your Bishopsgate restaurant and previously I have considered using your restaurant for a business lunch or dinner, but I definitely would not be doing that now as I would not want to be embarrassed in front of any clients who I would have taken.", " ", "I await your response to our numerous concerns.", " ", "Regards"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r545679417", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Family Christmas dinner and show.", "diner_date": " December 2017", "rating_date": "7 December 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "markbG7756PH", "reviewer_origin": ["Lowestoft, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "53"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "24"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r545679417-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Impressive venue..very theatrical like an old gentleman\u2019s club... blood red walls and plaid wallpaper..a huge wall of whisky \u2026!!naked lady paintings very tasteful. ", " Certainly up there with places to go...not cheap! But hey you don\u2019t do it every week....?", " Very good service very good food expensive wine....(geez be careful......) and watch out for the additional service charge which is discretionary.....?!!", " Haggis n Neeps Belly of Pork and a Panna cotta plus an excellent tribute act Frank and Dean The Vegas Show ....", "Scottish oak smoked salmon, wild venison carpaccio, crispy Szechuan pepper and chilli squid.....mains rib eye steak, turkey wrapped in parma ham and a crab salmon and haddock fishcake.... cheeseboard,sticky toffee chocolate cup and Christmas pudding...a bit of dancing ....excellent time was had by all\u2026what an evening...unforgettable. Thank you Boisdale\u2026. (A bottle of chocolate block red from SA.....\u00a380!!!!! In Waitrose \u00a321.99!! )of course you don\u2019t have to buy it......please try it it\u2019s an experience.... "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r544561918", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "A Touch of Scotland in Canary Wharf", "diner_date": " November 2017", "rating_date": "2 December 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Brazingo", "reviewer_origin": ["Sao Paulo, SP"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "98"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "33"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r544561918-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Boisdale was recommended by a friend and it lived up to expectations. We ate in the bar, and there is restaurant with live music on the floor above. The bar has an extensive menu with something for everyone. Even though a Saturday night, the service was excellent, with a full house. The food is well presented and the meals were excellent. Their steaks are superb and the duck was wonderful. ", "Boisdale has one the most comprehensive single malt whisky menus I have every found. They also have an outside terrace with heaters, serving food, drink and cigars, and they have a walk-in cigar humidor with a wide selection of cigars. I will certainly return to this restaurant."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r545717003", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Christmas party for the team.", "diner_date": " December 2017", "rating_date": "7 December 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "TariqJ4", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "60"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "18"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "10", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r545717003-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["The atmosphere and location is worth it, the restaurant has an amazing view of Cabot Square and with the Christmas tree lights provide a very pleasant view for the evening. However having made an effort to get there on time we did find the service sporadic, pretty hit and miss. There were issues with the wine and the times between the starter and main over 40 minutes - they were busy but it was surprising. I'd go again but only for the location and live music - the service was very unfortunate. I expect the waiters to be more attentive and circumspect - this was a company treat."]}
