{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r512382257", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Too many supplements", "diner_date": " August 2017", "rating_date": "13 August 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "JeffnCarol_Surrey", "reviewer_origin": ["London, England, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "88"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "61"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r512382257-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Went here on Friday night as a group of 5 ladies. We had prebooked a table for dinner and the music at \u00a339.50 a head and booked ahead for free flowing prosecco for 2 hours at \u00a315 (each although the waiter wasn't aware of the prosecco booking) ", "When you walk in there is a distinct smell of vomit which does disappear thank goodness in the actual venue. Staff were great if a little slow to begin with. 4 choices of starter, 2 of which had a supplement. Choice of 4 mains, burger a \u00a34 supplement, steak an \u00a38 supplement !!!! Guys that's too much. Food was good, music was good, lose the supplements"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r522975537", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Is there anything worse than appalling? ", "diner_date": " September 2017", "rating_date": "9 September 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "KrugerC", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "251"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "102"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r522975537-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["If there is then it must apply to our experience tonight. ", "We came here previously to see Mud Morganfield and It was a great evening. We mistakenly thought that was the norm and came back with some VIP and international guests tonight. The Jive Aces were performing. ", "The service was dreadful. I ordered a Jeroboam of champagne, a bottle of white and a bottle of red. The waitress disappeared for no less than 40 minutes before coming back with nothing and telling me the Jeroboam was out of stock as was the bottle of white. The red was available but they didn't bring that whilst we tried to resolve the other missing bottles. An hour and a quarter after we had been seated we got a drink. ", "Then there was the food, or lack thereof. Most of us (9 people) ordered steaks. Pretty simple to do. Except the meals were served peace meal with one of our guests getting his main course 30 minutes after everyone else. ", "It took so long to get our drinks and food we ran out of time to even consider dessert. ", "Coffees, teas? Not even offered. ", "The band - the Jive Aces - just not anywhere near the same league as Ginger Baker (#3 drummer in Rolling Stone magazines top 100 drummers of all time). Poor. Repetitive. Desperate. ", "I don't say these things idly. It's my job. I travel the world eating at decent restaurants and signing iconic people. Boisdale makes a big thing about Jools Holland running their music. I know Jools and have many him many times through a mutual friend. I cannot believe Jools was involved in tonight's booking. ", "We made the mistake of taking a good, Australian singer to Boisdale tonight based on our very good experience with Mud Morganfield. It was a mistake and we will never, ever put out foot in there again. ", "We complained to the management and they were totally disinterested. I was so cross I had the 'optional' \u00a3350 service charge taken off my bill. ", "This is obviously for tourists who have no idea what London, decent food, good service or entertainment is about. ", "Appalling is a favourable comment."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r521840362", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Fabulous Sunday lunch", "diner_date": " September 2017", "rating_date": "6 September 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "penni b", "reviewer_origin": ["Malaga, Spain"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "171"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "45"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r521840362-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Service impeccable food excellent, music just right great menu great cocktails and a really nice relaxing Sunday lunch can't fault it would have been better with more customers maybe would have created more atmosphere, but no complaints about anything super will definitely return."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r521439342", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Best steak on the Wharf ", "diner_date": " September 2017", "rating_date": "5 September 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Y9066IPpaulc", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "62"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "33"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r521439342-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Met friends after work in Canary Wharf bad robot or is giant robot and Mrs C came down from Suffolk for the evening , anyway it was busy and drink \u00a3\u00a3\u00a3\u00a3 at bad robot so we decided on food - Boisdale was suggested by other friend - what a surprise !! It's tucked away in what appears an unassuming office building, if that exists on the Wharf ! turn out of the lift wow - great decor and atmosphere jazz after 9:45 , sadly we didn't stay for the jazz - needed to be in the office Saturday for a bit , food was really good best steak I have had for a long time other meals also great - good wine selection lots of different choices When we left around. 9:30 the place was buzzing must try and arrange a return and later sitting for the Music"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r516678616", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Distinctly underwhelming", "diner_date": " August 2017", "rating_date": "23 August 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Brian M", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "832"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "350"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "20", "20"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r516678616-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["This is a huge barn and that only refers to the 2nd floor restaurant and facilities. Dark wood and rich red colours may be good for night time entertainment but not appealing on a sultry, late summer day. Seated by the window but view of neighbouring office windows and walls did not excite. Our waiter was poorly trained and had difficulty explaining the various beers/lagers available. Later he knocked over and broke a glass on the table and then returned and did the same with a beer bottle - fortunately empty and glass too thick to break.", "Food expensive and lacking any flair. My starter of spicy squid (\u00a39.75) featured rubbery strips which over coated and a pink sauce. Not impressed. Had high hopes of the 28 day aged 12oz rib-eye (\u00a332.00) cooked medium rare but again poor quality meat for such a price. The steak was not tender and had no great flavour so why all the fuss about its provenance. Sweet potato chips dredged through paprika (\u00a34.75) were edible but much too thin to impart the lovely flavour of this super vegetable.", "I was a guest so had to keep my views under wraps lest offending my host who obviously thought he was bring us to the best restaurant in Canary Wharf. Yet another disappointing \"big\" lunch outing"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r515109260", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Bit of a let down", "diner_date": " August 2017", "rating_date": "19 August 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "davmon650", "reviewer_origin": ["Bedford, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "5"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "40", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r515109260-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Went to Boisdale Canary Wharf on a Tuesday evening so didn't expect it to be too busy. We paid the music charge and had a meal before the jazz band came on. The main music room on Floor 2 was not very full at all. There was an event going on in the next room which was quite bustling and every time someone came through the adjoining door, the music was slightly drowned out, as it was right next to the stage. There was also a very noisy event coincidental on the floor below (the Terrace, I think) which was so loud and booming, that the floor almost shook and the bass could be heard above the jazz band! The waiter service was very good but they were very quiet, however, I received the wrong food in my starter. The main course 12 hour cooked lamb was tender but overpoweringly herbed and I could not eat it all. Overall, disappointing for a club with such high expectation."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r521966896", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Dinner and Music event", "diner_date": " August 2017", "rating_date": "6 September 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "N3775IGsusanb", "reviewer_origin": ["Purley, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "4"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r521966896-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Boisdale is a terrific place to go for a romantic dinner with live music. Book a table where you fancy and have a two course meal, wine and whisky that leaves a lingering taste for hours.... or add a third course. Even the Angus steak hamburger is excellent, the steak is worth paying extra for it. We saw a Salsa style band with a nod towards the Buena Vista Social Club from Cuba, where they would like you to show off your moves and get with the rhythm. If you have a craving for haggis, go A La Carte and have it as a starter. Thereafter you will be hooked, and have to go back. With my Scottish ancestry it's a must. At lunchtime you feel as if you are in a Scottish mansion in the highlands rather than the London Docklands, with stags adorning the walls. A treat!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r502976991", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Excellent beef", "diner_date": " July 2017", "rating_date": "17 July 2017", "answer_text": ["Hello Paul s, ", "I am glad to hear that you enjoyed the recent function you attended here at Boisdale Of Canary Wharf. Your kind words about the food have been well received by our kitchen team. ", "Thank you for taking the time to let us know how you enjoyed it, hopefully we will see you again soon.", "Kind Regards,", "Jenny Hughes"], "reviewer_pseudo": "213pauls", "reviewer_origin": ["Gerrards Cross, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "207"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "110"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r502976991-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Attended a busy function here in early July and the food was as you'd expect very good indeed. Main course featured an extremely tasty and tender roast fillet. Cheese was also rather good"]}
