{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r422444805", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Sunday Lunch at Boisdale Canary Wharf", "diner_date": " September 2016", "rating_date": "26 September 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Elaine R", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "132"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "38"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "30", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r422444805-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Booked this for lunch for my birthday after visiting Sherlock Unlock. The venue is beautiful once you get in but we didn't realise it was inside a kind of precinct where the trains run from so had a bit of trouble finding it. We ate in the restaurant and were served by an excellent waiter called Tim. He was brilliant, very helpful, courteous and pleasant throughout. We all choice a variety of dishes from the menu but didn't opt for the three course fixed price menu. Overall the food was very nice and most people enjoyed it, however, we did have to complain about the chicken as my husband's piece has blood in it and two of my other guests who had the same dish advised their chicken was pink/red so did not want to finish their food. They were all offered alternative meat, as the restaurant had run out of chicken, but two declined as were already full from the remainder of the meal but my husband did order the pork. Everyone who had the pork or fish dishes said their food was lovely but those that ordered the beef said it was tough and a bit grisly. Considering the beef was priced at a premium, this was very disappointing. The desserts, coffee and drinks were all excellent but the issues with the mains was upsetting, especially as this was somewhere I had chosen for my birthday to celebrate with friends. I was also surprised that the manager of the restaurant only came over to us on the first complaint about my husband's chicken. The two, later complaints, received no acknowledgment. I would recommend for the lovely ambience, music and mostly the food was good but I think the restaurant is short staffed as our waiter, although attentive as he could be was clearly serving a number of other tables, as were the other staff, and all struggling to keep on top of the demands of good service."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r422114977", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Good food and music, poor service", "diner_date": " September 2016", "rating_date": "25 September 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "GillMasefield", "reviewer_origin": ["Pontefract, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "106"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "56"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "20", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r422114977-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["The food here was very nice and well presented. It was my first taste of haggis, and i must say it was nice.", "The live music was also very good.", "The service of the food was also good, but when it came to drinks, the service was appaling. We got a drink when we first arrived and sat with an empty glass the rest of the night. We couldn't get the attention of anyone, despite putting our hands up like schoolchildren. We gave up and left. We told them when we paid the bill and they waived the service charge"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r417803620", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Birthday Sunday Lunch at Jazz Brunch", "diner_date": " September 2016", "rating_date": "13 September 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "PJBeck", "reviewer_origin": ["Ascot, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "5"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "5"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r417803620-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["First time at this venue. Like the Belgravia Restaurant very much and been many times so decided to try Sunday Jazz Brunch for my Birthday. Had family party of 11. Good things include the spacious interior but still had atmosphere and the musicians were good. Unfortunately in anybody's book 4 hours for lunch is v. poor service. It took over an hour to make an order. By the time we were finished the jazz trio had long since left the building. The food was OK but the roast did leave the impression it was an end of the day quality. Had an unprovoked apology from our waiter even though we did not complain. Hoped for a similar acknowledgement when the bill came but no such luck! Probably won't go back."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r425490490", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Nice meal, big portions", "diner_date": " October 2016", "rating_date": "6 October 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "gracefairlie", "reviewer_origin": ["East Kilbride, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "42"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "15"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r425490490-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Went with my adult son to the bar/ terrace for dinner . I ate from \u00a312-95 set menu : haggis and fillet steak. Son had a very large burger. Nice bottle of wine and enjoyed the experience . "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r408532125", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Sunday lunch jazz", "diner_date": " August 2016", "rating_date": "22 August 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "X3880UEdavidt", "reviewer_origin": ["Leeds, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "166"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "72"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r408532125-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["The set three course lunch on Sunday is not cheap but is really good quality.The portions are large and I really enjoyed the haggis the Yorkshire pudding and it's great to see bread sauce with chicken. The British cheese trolley is a real treat. The wines are a bit limited but all good quality. The service tailed off so that even after ordering and receiving coffee and then the bill we were still waiting for dessert plates to be cleared. That needs to improve. If you want to talk rather than listen to jazz, it is quite loud on certain tables, and when we went it was the more discordant style of jazz rather than laid back. I think we would go for the food but go when there is no music."]}
