{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r341349385", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Slightly odd - good for groups", "diner_date": " December 2015", "rating_date": "20 January 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Emer K", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "76"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "27"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r341349385-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I'm slightly mystified by Boisdale. I've been to the floor with the Grill restaurant (tarten carpet and nude photos) and with a bigger group to the main restaurant (big bar, treacle-slow service). The food is hit and miss but the location is great. It comes across as a great place for a lad's lunch - perhaps that's the aim. I wouldn't object to going again, but I don't think I would push for it. I can't comment on the jazz nights, but I do get the feeling that the main business is around this and similar events, rather than lunches (which is what I've been here for)."]}
