{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r131045060", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Top spot!", "diner_date": " May 2012", "rating_date": "31 May 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Michellesmith9", "reviewer_origin": ["Northampton, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "77"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "77"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "40", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r131045060-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Great food, great service, great atmosphere and pretty good music too. Thoroughly recommended."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r130207897", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great Birthday Night!", "diner_date": " May 2012", "rating_date": "19 May 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Bett76", "reviewer_origin": ["Miami, Florida"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "195"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "83"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r130207897-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We went there for just one reason, so my husband could enjoy on his birthday smoking his cigars while having a cognac. Looking for places where he could smoke in London, we came across Boisdale, which also happens to have a restaurant and one of the biggest whiskey bar in the world (as they say). So I made reservation for dinner. I have to say what a great surprise when I actually saw the restaurant. I wasn't expecting much, actually, but decoration was nice, table setting was first class, and food was good. For the first time in months my husband got his steak just as he likes it. Waitress was very nice, excellent wine, ambience was perfect! We really had a great evening. We did not stay for the show, but what we got to hear, music was very nice too.", "We then went to the terrace, so we could smoke our cigars, something almost inexistent in restaurants nowadays (having to smoke by the door, at the sidewalk, and cigars cannot be enjoyed like that).", "The check, taking aside the drinks, was very good priced, for the quality and the experience we had. Drinks are expensive everywhere, and since it was a special occasion, we were prepared to spend!", "One thing though that I did realized, is that I found Boisdale on the internet described as one of the top places where cigar aficionados can go an enjoy in London. But actually, we were the only ones smoking cigars, everyone else was smoking cigarettes, not that we mind, but it seems that real cigar aficionados don't go there."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r131982256", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "I was really looking forward to this place, but left disappointed", "diner_date": " May 2012", "rating_date": "14 June 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "kevinrwilson", "reviewer_origin": ["Heswall, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "153"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "61"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "20", "30", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r131982256-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I took some friends for dinner as we all like Jazz, and the concept sounded interesting. Our first complaint was the pricing of the wines, they were ridiculously expensive. The service was ok, but lacked warmth and the food was ok but nothing brilliant. I was so looking forward to having dinner here but left really disappointed."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r132164440", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "A great evenings entertainment", "diner_date": " June 2012", "rating_date": "17 June 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "GillyCG12", "reviewer_origin": ["Essex, UK"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "68"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "43"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r132164440-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Our first visit to this venue (birthday), we booked premium seating in the restaurant, which allowed us to keep the table all night for the band. Check them out they were called The Congo faith healers, they are on You tube and have their own website. All I can say is absolutely brilliant, their music was spot on and really entertaining. The service from arrival to when we left was top class, nothing was too much trouble, there was a great atmosphere. The food was delicious and there was an amazing menu of wines should you want them, we had the house Rose, really nice.", "To keep costs down you could dine downstairs in the Oyster bar downstairs and then see the entertainment, this still allowed a good view of the band. Not cheap but good value for the money."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r135391325", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Might look elsewhere next time", "diner_date": null, "rating_date": "26 July 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "dougz_22", "reviewer_origin": ["Parkland, Florida"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "26"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "8"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "30", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r135391325-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Well, it was ok. On a gorgeous London day, everyone wanted to be outside and we didn't care as all we wanted to do was eat so we opted to be the only ones eating on the first level indoors. The servers were otherwise focused on the throngs of people on the terrace (can't say as I blame them!) and we were forgotten about \"a little\". Not a crime but not bringing us back, either."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r135777121", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great place for live music and food", "diner_date": " July 2012", "rating_date": "30 July 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Q9011FPdonw", "reviewer_origin": ["Maldon, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "211"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "124"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r135777121-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We visited for a birthday celebration and to see The Jessica Lauren 4 and Jocelyn Brown. By booking a table we not only enjoyed great live music but also had a very pleasant meal. The menu had a decent variety and the quality was very good ( try the excellent cheese board!). Our server was first rate and the overall attention to customer service was very good. If you are into whiskey there is an outstanding whiskey bar. A great place to see live music (Jools Holland is the patron) and enjoy a meal at the same time. If you are driving to the venue the Canary Wharf car park is good value after 6.00pm."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r135973451", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Good food", "diner_date": " August 2012", "rating_date": "1 August 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Peter T", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "558"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "169"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "30", "20", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r135973451-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["This is only really a 'good' rather than 'very good' as one or two elements were missing. Great location and wonderfully laid out seating. We were in the restaurant rather than the brasserie and were met by a very friendly lady who showed us to our table but we then had to wait 15 minutes for a pre lunch drink. Menu was good and there was also a fixed price menu which was extremely reasonable and had good options - 2 courses for \u00a319.75. The main menu looked a bit expensive in places, eg \u00a330 for sea bass. The wine list was a bit on the pricey side too and if you moved off the 'house' list you were straight into the \u00a340 per bottle territory. Starter was amazing (haggis, neaps and tatties - it does have a Scottish theme after all) and portion sizes were perfect. My only real grumble was the service which was a bit average -our main courses were brought out but our starter plates were still in front of us in spite of us having finished some 15 minutes earlier."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r137369422", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "2nd visit even better than first - if that's possible", "diner_date": null, "rating_date": "16 August 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Hoylel", "reviewer_origin": ["North east. England"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "27"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "9"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r137369422-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["This time was launch of a Jools Holland jazz festival. Evening was amazing. Superb Food, perfect wine, great atmosphere all supported by the very professional staff. Can't wait for visit number 3. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r126031857", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Modern Boisdale's", "diner_date": " March 2012", "rating_date": "13 March 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Mmiller2367", "reviewer_origin": ["Vienna, Austria"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "25"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "9"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r126031857-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I normally frequent Boisdale's in Bishopsgate as it is more convenient. The service, wine and fine were excellent. The only weird aspect was that they put a abridged menu on our table first and I had to ask for the familiar menu. Maybe it was because it was Monday. There was live music starting with Piano and moving to Jazz. It did not overwhelm our conversation and created a good atmosphere for a Monday night."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r126167819", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Could do better", "diner_date": " March 2012", "rating_date": "16 March 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "accipitor", "reviewer_origin": ["Winchester, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "301"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "186"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "10", "20", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r126167819-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Both steaks over cooked but very tasty. Staff try and up sell relentlessly with a very overpriced wine list. No doubt their location in 'banker central' is the reason. Note Hawksmoor and Barbecoa have better wine choices to suit a range of budgets. Our waiter lost interest once the 'selling' process was complete and did not top up our water. It took ages to get the bill in an empty restaurant while staff were carrying chairs around us. Also disliked the bare tables around us at the start of our lunch. Great size room and view needs to be matched with much sharper service."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r126089355", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Beware of the noise!", "diner_date": " March 2012", "rating_date": "14 March 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "eastendbird", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "78"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "66"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "20", "50", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r126089355-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We went on a Friday evening, having booked weeks in advance to see one of our favourite jazz singers. The venue is large and impressive, with amazing views of Cabot Square. Service from the start was efficient and very friendly, I really can't fault it. My partner ordered from the cheaper \"Jacobite\" menu whilst I went a la carte. Both our starters were good - Colchester oysters and the potted mackerel. The mains less so - an indifferent burger and a very small portion of plaice in a strangely bitter sauce. We had cocktails, a bottle of wine, coffees and a cognac: \u00a3150. I've definitely had better food for less. But on top of that we had paid \u00a350 for our tickets and here came the really annoying part. Half of the room was clearly not interested in listening to the band and talked all the way through, to the frustration of those of us that did want to listen and indeed to the singer and the band themselves. Even towards the end, when we managed to get the whole room quiet , it became clear there was also a dull roar (coming up through an internal staircase in the centre of the room) from the bar down below. My advice - if you want a venue in London to watch jazz: go to Ronnie Scotts, the food is better and you can hear the music properly. If you go to Boisdales, go for the view and eat from the Jacobite menu - its better value for money."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r126178301", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Average food at above average prices", "diner_date": " March 2012", "rating_date": "16 March 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "LadyMills_12", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "10"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "10"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "20", "50", "20"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r126178301-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I had been really looking forward to dining in the 2nd floor restaurant at Boisdale Canary Wharf as had heard (and read) some good things about the place. We chose from the Jacobite menu which was \u00a319.95 a head. The starter of mackeral was ok but my main course of chicken was rather bland. Drinks were ultra expensive, e.g. small vodka and tonic in a short glass was \u00a310 which I thought rather excessive. Staff were very well trained and polite. We were also charged \u00a33.50 for listening to a piano player for 30 mins whilst the music in the bar was stlll playing. I probably won't visit again as I think you can get better food in Ronnie Scotts or Jazz Cafe."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r128896618", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Do NOT go here for the music", "diner_date": " April 2012", "rating_date": "27 April 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "11diner11", "reviewer_origin": ["Greater London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "298"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "160"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "10", "40", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r128896618-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Hard to express how angry I am about last night's visit to the Boisdale without descending into profanities. Not, I hasten to add, with the venue itself. We were driving, and for London the parking at Canary Wharf is surprisingly cheap. If travelling by the Docklands Light Railway one can walk off the platform, go down an escalator, and be in the Boisdale in about a minute. ", "Very swish and well appointed, the food was excellent - which it should be for the price. Starters, the potted shrimps and the crab tian, were very pleasant. My rump steak was absolutely excellent: tender, exceedingly well flavoured, and cooked spot on for the 'rare' requested. Best steak I've had anywhere since a meal at Gaucho's last year. Mrs P's langoustine main was very nice she assured me. The only fault - a minor one - was in one of the sides: the mushrooms were somewhat over-cooked.", "Drinks are on the expensive side. The House wine list is quite short, and not particularly interesting to be frank. Mark up is 300-400%. However the rest of a very lengthy list has two prices: one for members, and another with a hefty surcharge for everyone else. Doubtless the Boisdale would like to assert they are offering a 'discount' for members, but at those mark ups it just feels like a bit of additional fleecing, so we went for a bottle off the House list. It was nothing better than ok, and not worth the price charged.", "We'd missed Ruby Turner's recent sessions at Ronnie Scott's, with all three evenings sold out. But here was an opportunity to catch up with one of our favourite artists, a British R&B and Soul legend for around 35 years. And now we come to what has me seething still: the clientele. Despite having a table right by the stage, even there one could not avoid an incessant hubbub of loud conversations (which just got louder and louder as people competed with the music), people chatting on mobiles, and the man on the table behind us (who had presumably also paid \u00a3120 for him and his wife to theoretically listen to Ruby) talking at full volume non-stop throught the ENTIRETY of the first set. Twice she appealed to the audience, the first time in a light-hearted pleasant way, the second more openly clearly utterly fed up, but there was no respite from the boorish, rude, crass disrespect to a great artist. Oh well, it's money in the bank, what the hell: so understandably the second set was rushed through with as much disinterest as 80% of the audience were paying her. She could not wait to get off the stage, with several numbers curtailed from their usual length, and justifiably did not return to provide an encore.", "One might say that people, having paid their money, can do what they want; but for the life of me can't see why so many doubled the price of their meal just to talk over the act.", "Of course it may have been a one off, but not giving it a second chance to have an evening ruined: never bothering with the Boisdale for a musical dining event again."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r126583397", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Perfect steaks associated with great music", "diner_date": " February 2012", "rating_date": "24 March 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "rogerkem", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "228"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "111"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r126583397-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Recommend by a colleague I went there for live jazz music, but as promised the food was also excellent. Before the evening show a piano player provided a great background sound. ", "The menu offers a great variety of steaks and fish. The steak I had was superb as well as the dessert. The wine list is also remarkable with reasonable prices. ", "Extraordinary is the whiskey selection. I haven never seen such a variety of whiskeys in any bar in the world I have been before. I definitely will stop by again next time I will be in London."]}
