{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r126974816", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "What a treat...", "diner_date": " March 2012", "rating_date": "30 March 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "MagicNumba", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "96"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "105"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r126974816-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Really enjoyed our night at Boisdales, what a wonderful restaurant and atmosphere. We had a table overlooking the fountains in Cabot Square, wow.... We are Londoners and felt very proud to be in such an exclusive area, funnily enough eating in a very nice Scottish restaurant, will definitely go back."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r127452656", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Boisdale: overpriced but cool venue", "diner_date": " April 2012", "rating_date": "8 April 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "John C", "reviewer_origin": ["Cambridge, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "13"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "16"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "40", "30", "20"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r127452656-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Went to see a jazz quartet. Food very overpriced for its quality but staff helpful and attentive. Cool venue and atmosphere. If you want to chat during the music, take a window seat overlooking the square."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r119470200", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Drifters tribute night - great food, but watch out for the drunken old people", "diner_date": " October 2011", "rating_date": "19 October 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "LikkleNitty", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "25"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "20"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "30", "20", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r119470200-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["My partner and I recently went to the Drifters night in Boisdale, Canary Wharf.", "The reception from the staff was great and we were swiftly led to our table directly in front of the stage. Premier seats were \u00a335 per person, which we thought was reasonable.", "It was quite busy as it was 8pm on a Friday night, so we waited patiently to be served after being seated. We waited for a good 15-20 minutes before the maitre d\u2019 noticed our growing impatience and came and took our drinks and food order.", "The band were excellent and very entertaining, although the feed from the band itself was a little too loud and overpowered the singers voices a bit.", "Within a couple minutes of the band starting at 9pm, a group of about 8 women got up and started dancing (badly) in front of us. The stage is quite low (about a foot off the ground) and there was approximately 5 feet of open space between our table and the front of the stage; there wasn\u2019t a huge amount of space available, bearing in mind that about 20 feet away to the right of the stage was where the kitchen was located and where the waiting staff brought out hot food.", "I was annoyed that these women were prancing around in front of us, and totally obscuring our view of the singers with their backsides. If I wanted to see middle-aged women dancing, I would go to a Wetherspoons, where we wouldn\u2019t need to pay \u00a335 per person for this \u201cprivilege\u201d. There was a very drunk woman, who was wobbling and flailing her way around this area throughout the performance. I didn\u2019t want to watch her, but I was distracted by her antics the entire time, especially the part where she fell over and smacked her head on the bar. These drunk women gave me the impression that I was in some low-rate, dingy pub, which I\u2019m sure is not the image Boisdale is peddling.", "We mentioned the drunk people to the maitre d\u2019 and he said, \u201cWe encourage this interaction.\u201d Interaction?! This wasn\u2019t interaction, this was the cast of Shameless after a heavy night out. ", "Tip to those who want to see any performances at this restaurant/venue: sit in the middle. It\u2019s cheaper and you won\u2019t have drunken old people falling on you, slamming back their drinks and breaking their glasses on your table.", "Other than that, the food was brilliant, and the dessert (Bourbon cheesecake) was even better."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r125789722", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Be Aware of the \"Jazz Charge\"", "diner_date": " December 2011", "rating_date": "8 March 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Hopstepper", "reviewer_origin": ["Stenhousemuir, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "98"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "45"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "40", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r125789722-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We booked a Christmas meal for 9 people but only 8 could show up. We were charged for 9 but that was OK. Live music is played and there is a discretionary charge of \u00a315 per head. We were charged 9 instead of 8 - we could have complained but we were entertaining clients.", "Food is good, views are great, whisky choice is astonishing but prices are really high."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r121457538", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "lovely venue but.....", "diner_date": " December 2011", "rating_date": "6 December 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "molins", "reviewer_origin": ["Barcelona"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "7"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "9"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "40", "40", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r121457538-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I love the idea of the venue- good music and a great meal. And that\u00b4s what we got at Boisdale. I pre-booked our table via web page for ( 2 Dec) gbp20 pp. The set menu is a little limited I had the lambs lettuce and salad cream(that\u00b4s all it was!) thena burger which was ok ! my husband had ravioli and steak with a lovely mushroom sauce (not on set menu) you have to order a side dish seperately !we enjoyed a bottle of merlot and a cheese board and cocktails to finish. The service was good and it should be! we noticed when re returned to our hotel that we paid 12.5% 16.76 for (optional) service charge !! on our 134.10 dinner. I think is a little expensive with booking fee as well. I would like to add that we loved the music but the audience didn\u00b4t pay much attention to the band due to dinner being served throughout which I thought was a little rude and a shame because it was great music. We come from Barcelona and this would go down a storm but half the price !!!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r120398765", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Great addition to Canary Wharf", "diner_date": null, "rating_date": "9 November 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "foxbat", "reviewer_origin": ["Ascot, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "364"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "245"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "30", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r120398765-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Boisdales is a brave new restaurant that I have eaten at twice, both times with great satisfaction. I say brave as it is massive , with a big jazz club restaurant laden with atmosphere and then you have a trendy oyster bar and cigar terrace.", "The decor is fabulous -sort of Scottish chic and the food faultless."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r122857266", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Good food, excellent service and nice Jazz live band!", "diner_date": " January 2012", "rating_date": "10 January 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "fr_phil", "reviewer_origin": ["France"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "22"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "27"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r122857266-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["A very good beef steak (the rest was good too), well located in the middle of Canary Wharf, an excellent service provided by Philippe and the lovely company of the Live Jazz Band made our dinner a very enjoyable one.", "Make sure to check the schedule for the live band as I am not sure they have it every night.", "If you are into whiskys, they have a huge selection that will most likely please you.", "A place I would recommend."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r121889341", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Add this to your must do list bon viveurs.", "diner_date": " December 2011", "rating_date": "19 December 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "drmalcolm", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "59"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "65"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r121889341-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["If this is what you like rent your own cigar box, join and book your premium table, hear adequate always , somttimes phenomenal jazz and headliners, hear Rat Pack tribute Shows (best Frank Sinatra I have seen), stuff your face with oysters, seafood, best steaks and occasionally wagu, foi gras (if your conscious will let you) and live life to the full. If its on the menu they will alter eat or do it differently. I used to have foi gras to start, (I know I shouldnt) and will stop in the New Year. Grouse in season, ask for pink breast and crispy leg , with extra game chips, bread sauce , bacon and gravy. YUMMY. The oyster bar downstairs is great for lunch or pre show if thats all you want, and they have outside terraces and supply members rugs to use if they dont want to sit in the cigar room where you can only smoke ones bought there, but outside anything goes. Different from the one in Belgravia and like them both equally. However if I had to choose probably this rates higher. Say I sent you, Last time there I finished Jerry Springers cigar when he had only had 6 puffs of a \u00a3100 aged cuban. terrible or what, but as a kid I picked up dogends!!! Service can be variable, but if it is ask to speak to the Manager, he will be mortified and tries even harder!!!!"]}
