{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r124222267", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "A posh gentlemen's club", "diner_date": " February 2012", "rating_date": "6 February 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "fireflies_w", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "67"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "34"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "40", "50", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r124222267-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Posh decor and great service. Food is on average just okay - steak tartare was completely bland, the fish cake however was very good. Chilled bread & butter pudding was interesting but not impressive taste-wise."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r125316424", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Great night ruined by poor service", "diner_date": " February 2012", "rating_date": "27 February 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "tigru8haiduc", "reviewer_origin": ["St Albans, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "19"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "39"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "10", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r125316424-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Very impressed with the ambiance and the wisky bar. The buena vista social club tribute was very good. Food was amazing, best burger ever and the cheesecake was heaven. Although the meet and greet was very nice, service on the other side was very poor. The sparkling wine came after we had eaten our oysters. Then we ordered teh food and just a bottle of house wine. When the starters came the wine and the bread had not been served. We told that to the food runner and the waiter came with the bread, still no wine. After we finished the starters we asked the hostess about the wine. After another wait the waiter came with a glass of white!! After another wait the bottle of white was brought , just before the mains. We ordered an espresso- whorible. No crema, over-extracted, you wouldn't expect this in a place like that. And finally when we asked for the bill we gto charged \u00a329.50 instead of 17.50 for the wine. Lost of staff around, I think they just need to get themselves organized. Obviously we didn't pay any service charge!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r114790477", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Might have been nice ......", "diner_date": " June 2011", "rating_date": "27 June 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "DAS4_11", "reviewer_origin": ["Aberdeen, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "5"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Atmosphere", "Service"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "10"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r114790477-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We went along to Boisdale CW to see if there were any tables available - they didn't actually say no, but in a very patronising manner indicated the oyster bar may have something for us. One of the staff (female)offered to go with us in the lift, and on the way pointed out that there was a cover charge for tables in the restaurant because of the music. We were so offended by a) the patronising attitude of the staff at the door and b) being spoken down to by the female member of staff that we decided we didn't really want to frequent such an establishment!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r114817410", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Style and Class combined", "diner_date": null, "rating_date": "28 June 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "ThierrySch", "reviewer_origin": ["Tschoen"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "24"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "25"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r114817410-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I was for the first time at BCW last night, Had nice cocktail on the terrace before dinner and live music in the restaurant. I was very surprised about the prices. The tickets were only \u00a320 per person and it was very compfy. Food was amazing and my wallet didn't suffer at all. Boisdale of Canary Wharf is not just for Bankers and city workers but also for a normal Bloke like me."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r116809256", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Bring earplugs. Am I showing my age?", "diner_date": " July 2011", "rating_date": "16 August 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Daenelle", "reviewer_origin": ["Oxford, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "198"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "108"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "30", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r116809256-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Well, when the music is playing, you need to treat this restaurant as a club, because it is LOUD. I guess what I am saying is that you need to be going not for the food or the company or the conversation, but for the music because everything else will be drowned out. That said, it's not many places that serve such tasty nosh while you listen to music ... and the food here IS good. It's also very expensive - but that's the Canary Wharf location. The location brings other complications: everyone in the room is wearing a suit and works at Canary Wharf. If those don't bother you, we really enjoyed our meal and the wine was great too."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r114698638", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Excellent jazz club in cwharf, recommended!", "diner_date": " June 2011", "rating_date": "24 June 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "TomG55", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "6"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r114698638-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Great service, decoration, food looks great, very good venue and programme; get a table near the window if u can for dinner @ 2 ;)"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r119347280", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Great traditional food, well cooked", "diner_date": " October 2011", "rating_date": "16 October 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "FoodloverLondon", "reviewer_origin": ["London"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "67"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "38"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "30", "30", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r119347280-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["When I first visited this restauarant when it first opened I was initially put off by the decor, which is all tartan and red. Psuedo Scottish highlands country house in a modern Canary Wharf building. However once it got dark the decor actually works, and the food was really good. I have been back several times for lunch and dinner since and the food has been superb everytime. ", "For my most recent visit i had the mini haggis followed by steak. I think the steak is probably their signature dish. The mini haggis i thoroughly recommend, and the steaks are always well cooked, tender and succulent. ", "They also have a good range of wine and of course the largest selection of whiskey in Europe. ", "I recommend it for lunch or dinner. The jazz starts at 9pm for which you are charged \u00a330. However if you get in there around 7ish you can be in and out by 9.30 and get a bit of the jazz without paying for a whole evening. Although if you like jazz then it's worth the \u00a330 for the whole evening. ", "There's also an oyster bar, and a cigar room. ", "For the quality of the food it is good value for money and a welcome addition to Canary Wharf. It's certainly on my list of regular haunts."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2180904", "id_comment": "g186338-d2180904-r116653737", "resto": "Boisdale_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2180904-Reviews-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Excellent 40th Birthday celebration venue", "diner_date": " August 2011", "rating_date": "13 August 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "OxiLondon", "reviewer_origin": ["West Wickham, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "11"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "8"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2180904-r116653737-Boisdale_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We were celebrating my boy-friend's 40th birthday there. We have been given a table with a nice view of the square and fountains below. The staff was very friendly and attentive. We arrived at 6.30pm to give us plenty of time to enjoy food and drink before the show starts at 9pm. The food was really good, one of our guest ordered stake and it tasted fantastic(as we all tried a small piece)! I regretted I didn't order myself, however my food was really good as well. Scottish haggis tasted delicious.", "The atmosphere was very vibranbt and robus. The show started at 9pm and it was a perfect addition to our night out. Everything just was spot on, tables far apart so it felt private, great food, nice view, really good service and amazing venue. Definately one of the best nights out I had for a long time and the best venue for big birthday celebrations. At the end we even danced for a bit next to the stage! ", "Top place! Thank you for a great experience!"]}
